<subSubSection lastPageId="5" pageId="1" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1323,1318,1905]" pageId="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,651,1558,1584]" pageId="1">
Description of the 
<typeStatus box="[544,651,1558,1584]" pageId="1">holotype</typeStatus>
</emphasis>
: Body length 
<quantity box="[820,914,1559,1585]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.85" pageId="1" unit="mm" value="285.0">285 µm</quantity>
; eyes absent according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Horning, D. S. &amp; Schuster, R. O. &amp; Grigarick, A. A." pageId="1" pagination="185 - 280" refId="ref4789" refString="Horning, D. S., Schuster, R. O. &amp; Grigarick, A. A. (1978) Tardigrada from New Zealand. New Zealand Journal of Zoology, 5, 185 - 280." type="journal article" year="1978">
Horning 
<emphasis box="[264,322,1599,1624]" italics="true" pageId="1">et al.</emphasis>
(1978)
</bibRefCitation>
. Median plate 3 present (
<figureCitation box="[703,800,1599,1625]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[264,367,1816,1840]" captionTargetBox="[382,1209,313,1794]" captionTargetId="figure-37@3.[379,1217,299,1795]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Echiniscus arthuri sp. nov. (holotype): A, B, details of the plate sculpture. Scale bar = 10 m." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5050053" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5050053/files/figure.png" pageId="1">Fig. 2 B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[812,859,1599,1625]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[264,368,1797,1821]" captionTargetBox="[394,1193,313,1781]" captionTargetId="figure-56@4.[394,1194,312,1781]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. A, B: Echiniscus arthuri sp. nov. (holotype): A, details of the plate sculpture; B, claws of the first three pairs of legs. C: Echiniscus merokensis, details of the plate sculpture. Scale bar = 10 m." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5050057" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5050057/files/figure.png" pageId="1">3 A</figureCitation>
); ventral plates absent. All dorsal plates with almost invisible small dots and pores of various shape and size (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Richters" authorityYear="1904" box="[1114,1244,1639,1664]" class="Heterotardigrada" family="Echiniscidae" genus="Echiniscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Echiniscoidea" pageId="1" phylum="Tardigrada" rank="species" species="merokensis">
<emphasis box="[1114,1244,1639,1664]" italics="true" pageId="1">merokensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
type). Head plate with anterior notch; neck plate narrow (
<figureCitation box="[910,1024,1679,1705]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[264,367,1816,1840]" captionTargetBox="[382,1209,313,1794]" captionTargetId="figure-37@3.[379,1217,299,1795]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Echiniscus arthuri sp. nov. (holotype): A, B, details of the plate sculpture. Scale bar = 10 m." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5050053" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5050053/files/figure.png" pageId="1">Fig. 2 A</figureCitation>
); scapular plate without smooth transversal bands; as in many species of 
<taxonomicName box="[829,956,1719,1744]" class="Heterotardigrada" family="Echiniscidae" genus="Echiniscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Echiniscoidea" pageId="1" phylum="Tardigrada" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[829,956,1719,1744]" italics="true" pageId="1">Echiniscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it is composed of three pieces, 
<emphasis box="[264,300,1759,1784]" italics="true" pageId="1">i.e.</emphasis>
, a larger central one and two smaller lateral pieces (
<figureCitation box="[919,1022,1759,1785]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[264,367,1816,1840]" captionTargetBox="[382,1209,313,1794]" captionTargetId="figure-37@3.[379,1217,299,1795]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Echiniscus arthuri sp. nov. (holotype): A, B, details of the plate sculpture. Scale bar = 10 m." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5050053" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5050053/files/figure.png" pageId="1">Fig. 2 A</figureCitation>
); each paired plate II and III with smooth transversal band (
<figureCitation box="[699,812,1799,1825]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[264,367,1816,1840]" captionTargetBox="[382,1209,313,1794]" captionTargetId="figure-37@3.[379,1217,299,1795]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Echiniscus arthuri sp. nov. (holotype): A, B, details of the plate sculpture. Scale bar = 10 m." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5050053" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5050053/files/figure.png" pageId="1">Fig. 2 B</figureCitation>
); terminal plate with two postero­lateral incisions, without smooth areas (
<figureCitation box="[652,747,1839,1865]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[264,368,1797,1821]" captionTargetBox="[394,1193,313,1781]" captionTargetId="figure-56@4.[394,1194,312,1781]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. A, B: Echiniscus arthuri sp. nov. (holotype): A, details of the plate sculpture; B, claws of the first three pairs of legs. C: Echiniscus merokensis, details of the plate sculpture. Scale bar = 10 m." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5050057" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5050057/files/figure.png" pageId="1">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
). Ventral surface with very fine, almost invisible dots.
</paragraph>
