<paragraph blockId="5.[264,1324,284,473]" pageId="5">
Lateral spines C and D, filaments E, dorsal filaments 
<superScript attach="left" box="[952,981,284,313]" fontSize="7" pageId="5">Cd</superScript>
and spines 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1122,1153,284,313]" fontSize="7" pageId="5">Dd</superScript>
are present in addition to the filaments A. An evident spine is present on the first pair of legs; a papilla and a fringe with obtuse teeth on the fourth pair of legs. The length of some structures is indicated in 
<tableCitation box="[408,495,407,433]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="5.[264,352,526,550]" captionText="TABLE 1. Dimensions (in m) of some structures of one specimen of Echiniscus arthuri sp. nov. (holotype) and of Echiniscus elainae sp. nov. and of E. nigripustulatus Horning et al., 1978." pageId="5">Table 1</tableCitation>
. External claws without spurs, each internal claw with an obvious spur (
<figureCitation box="[273,371,447,473]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[264,368,1797,1821]" captionTargetBox="[394,1193,313,1781]" captionTargetId="figure-56@4.[394,1194,312,1781]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. A, B: Echiniscus arthuri sp. nov. (holotype): A, details of the plate sculpture; B, claws of the first three pairs of legs. C: Echiniscus merokensis, details of the plate sculpture. Scale bar = 10 m." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5050057" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5050057/files/figure.png" pageId="5">Fig. 3 B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
