<subSubSection pageId="5" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[264,1323,1435,1904]" pageId="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,456,1435,1461]" pageId="5">Etymology:</emphasis>
The name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pilato &amp; Binda &amp; Lisi" authorityYear="2005" box="[607,690,1435,1460]" class="Heterotardigrada" family="Echiniscidae" genus="Echiniscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Echiniscoidea" pageId="5" phylum="Tardigrada" rank="species" species="arthuri">
<emphasis box="[607,690,1435,1460]" italics="true" pageId="5">arthuri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
derives from the locality where the 
<typeStatus box="[1160,1263,1435,1461]" pageId="5">holotype</typeStatus>
was found: Arthurs Pass National Park
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="6" pageId="5" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[264,1323,1435,1904]" pageId="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,435,1515,1541]" pageId="5">Remarks:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Pilato &amp; Binda &amp; Lisi, 2005" authorityName="Pilato &amp; Binda &amp; Lisi" authorityYear="2005" box="[443,660,1515,1540]" class="Heterotardigrada" family="Echiniscidae" genus="Echiniscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Echiniscoidea" pageId="5" phylum="Tardigrada" rank="species" species="arthuri" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[443,660,1515,1540]" italics="true" pageId="5">Echiniscus arthuri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[667,761,1515,1541]" pageId="5">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[667,761,1515,1541]" pageId="5" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Murray" authorityYear="1910" box="[916,1162,1515,1540]" class="Heterotardigrada" family="Echiniscidae" genus="Echiniscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Echiniscoidea" pageId="5" phylum="Tardigrada" rank="species" species="velaminis">
<emphasis box="[916,1162,1515,1540]" italics="true" pageId="5">Echiniscus velaminis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having the sculpture of the terminal plate not very different from that of the other plates; it has smooth bands on paired plates II and III while 
<bibRefCitation author="Murray, J." box="[727,894,1595,1621]" pageId="5" pagination="83 - 185" refId="ref4898" refString="Murray, J. (1910) Tardigrada. British Antarctic Expedition 1907 - 1909. London, 1 (5), 83 - 185." type="journal article" year="1910">Murray (1910</bibRefCitation>
, p. 112) specified that “None of the plates has the surface markings interrupted by lines or bands”; it also differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Murray" authorityYear="1910" class="Heterotardigrada" family="Echiniscidae" genus="Echiniscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Echiniscoidea" pageId="5" phylum="Tardigrada" rank="species" species="velaminis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5">E. velaminis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having well­developed spurs on the internal claws; Murray specified “claws all without barbs”; he was an excellent observer and it is not believable that he would not have noted such well­developed spurs if they had been present.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[264,1323,1435,1904]" pageId="5">
The new species differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Beasley, 1999" authorityName="Beasley" authorityYear="1999" box="[675,1008,1795,1821]" class="Heterotardigrada" family="Echiniscidae" genus="Echiniscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Echiniscoidea" pageId="5" phylum="Tardigrada" rank="species" species="clevelandi">
<emphasis box="[675,831,1795,1820]" italics="true" pageId="5">E. clevelandi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Beasley, C. W." box="[841,1008,1795,1821]" pageId="5" pagination="135 - 138" refId="ref4655" refString="Beasley, C. W. (1999) A new species of Echiniscus (Tardigrada, Echiniscidae) from Northern Yunnan Province, China. Zoologischer Anzeiger, 238, 135 - 138." type="journal article" year="1999">
Beasley, 
<quantity box="[950,1008,1795,1821]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.07746" pageId="5" unit="in" value="1999.0">1999</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in the following features: fine plate dots almost invisible, appendage B absent, the appendages E and 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1243,1272,1835,1864]" fontSize="7" pageId="5">Cd</superScript>
are filaments.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[264,1323,283,1274]" pageId="6">
<taxonomicName authority="Pilato &amp; Binda &amp; Lisi, 2005" authorityName="Pilato &amp; Binda &amp; Lisi" authorityYear="2005" box="[312,530,284,309]" class="Heterotardigrada" family="Echiniscidae" genus="Echiniscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Echiniscoidea" pageId="6" phylum="Tardigrada" rank="species" species="arthuri" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[312,530,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="6">Echiniscus arthuri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[538,633,283,309]" pageId="6">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[538,633,283,309]" pageId="6" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Pilato, 1972" authorityName="Pilato" authorityYear="1972" box="[791,1063,284,310]" class="Heterotardigrada" family="Echiniscidae" genus="Echiniscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Echiniscoidea" pageId="6" phylum="Tardigrada" rank="species" species="carusoi">
<emphasis box="[791,912,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="6">E. carusoi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Pilato, G." box="[920,1063,284,310]" pageId="6" pagination="111 - 124" refId="ref4925" refString="Pilato, G. (1972) Prime osservazioni sui tardigradi delle Isole Egadi. Bollettino Accademia Gioenia Scienze Naturali, Catania, S. IV, XI, 5 - 6, 111 - 124." type="journal article" year="1972">
Pilato, 
<quantity box="[1005,1063,284,310]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.00888" pageId="6" unit="in" value="1972.0">1972</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in having pores more various in shape and size, in having a filament (not a spine) E. In addition, it is to be noted that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pilato" authorityYear="1972" box="[316,438,364,389]" class="Heterotardigrada" family="Echiniscidae" genus="Echiniscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Echiniscoidea" pageId="6" phylum="Tardigrada" rank="species" species="carusoi">
<emphasis box="[316,438,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="6">E. carusoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
only exceptionally has lateral spines C and D, and that the combination of filaments A, C, D, E, 
<superScript attach="left" box="[519,546,404,430]" fontSize="6" pageId="6">Cd</superScript>
and 
<superScript attach="left" box="[603,632,404,430]" fontSize="6" pageId="6">Dd</superScript>
has never been found in this species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[264,1323,283,1274]" pageId="6">
The new species differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Claxton, 1996" authorityName="Claxton" authorityYear="1996" box="[666,975,444,470]" class="Heterotardigrada" family="Echiniscidae" genus="Echiniscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Echiniscoidea" pageId="6" phylum="Tardigrada" rank="species" species="curiosus">
<emphasis box="[666,799,445,470]" italics="true" pageId="6">E. curiosus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Claxton, S." box="[808,975,444,470]" pageId="6" pagination="13 - 33" refId="ref4690" refString="Claxton, S. (1996) Sexual dimorphism in Australian Echiniscus (Tardigrada, Echiniscidae) with description of three new species. Zoological Journal Linnean Society, 116, 13 - 33." type="journal article" year="1996">
Claxton, 
<quantity box="[917,975,444,470]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.06984" pageId="6" unit="in" value="1996.0">1996</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in having the cuticular pores not regularly arranged around central dark areas of definite shape; in addition, the appendages E and 
<superScript attach="left" box="[483,510,524,551]" fontSize="6" pageId="6">Cd</superScript>
(often absent in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Claxton" authorityYear="1996" box="[707,839,525,550]" class="Heterotardigrada" family="Echiniscidae" genus="Echiniscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Echiniscoidea" pageId="6" phylum="Tardigrada" rank="species" species="curiosus">
<emphasis box="[707,839,525,550]" italics="true" pageId="6">E. curiosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) are filaments.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[264,1323,283,1274]" pageId="6">
<taxonomicName authority="Pilato &amp; Binda &amp; Lisi, 2005" authorityName="Pilato &amp; Binda &amp; Lisi" authorityYear="2005" box="[312,433,565,590]" class="Heterotardigrada" family="Echiniscidae" genus="Echiniscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Echiniscoidea" pageId="6" phylum="Tardigrada" rank="species" species="arthuri" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[312,433,565,590]" italics="true" pageId="6">E. arthuri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[446,546,564,590]" pageId="6">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[446,546,564,590]" pageId="6" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="(Doyere, 1840)" baseAuthorityName="Doyere" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[718,1039,565,591]" class="Heterotardigrada" family="Echiniscidae" genus="Echiniscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Echiniscoidea" pageId="6" phylum="Tardigrada" rank="species" species="testudo">
<emphasis box="[718,841,565,590]" italics="true" pageId="6">E. testudo</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Doyere, L." box="[863,1032,565,591]" pageId="6" pagination="269 - 361" refId="ref4725" refString="Doyere, L. (1840) Memoire sur les Tardigrades. Annales Sciences Naturelles (Zoologie), 14, 269 - 361." type="journal article" year="1840">Doyère, 1840</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
in details of the plate sculpture; in the presence of dorsal appendage 
<superScript attach="right" box="[838,868,605,634]" fontSize="7" pageId="6">Cd</superScript>
; in having shorter claws, and internal claws with more developed spurs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[264,1323,283,1274]" pageId="6">
It differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Maucci, 1983" authorityName="Maucci" authorityYear="1983" box="[490,830,688,714]" class="Heterotardigrada" family="Echiniscidae" genus="Echiniscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Echiniscoidea" pageId="6" phylum="Tardigrada" rank="species" species="lichenorum">
<emphasis box="[490,658,688,713]" italics="true" pageId="6">E. lichenorum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Maucci, W." box="[668,830,688,714]" pageId="6" pagination="257 - 261" refId="ref4849" refString="Maucci, W. (1983) Echiniscus bisculptus n. sp., del Marocco ed E. lichenorum n. sp., del Portogallo. Atti Societa italiana di Scienze naturali e Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Milano, 124, 257 - 261." type="journal article" year="1983">
Maucci, 
<quantity box="[772,830,688,714]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.03682" pageId="6" unit="in" value="1983.0">1983</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in lacking smooth bands on the scapular and terminal plates, in the presence of the appendage E, and in having more developed spurs on the internal claws.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[264,1323,283,1274]" pageId="6">
The new species differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Iharos, 1936" authorityName="Iharos" authorityYear="1936" box="[695,1034,808,834]" class="Heterotardigrada" family="Echiniscidae" genus="Echiniscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Echiniscoidea" pageId="6" phylum="Tardigrada" rank="species" species="bartramiae">
<emphasis box="[695,867,808,833]" italics="true" pageId="6">E. bartramiae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Iharos, G." box="[881,1034,808,834]" pageId="6" pagination="218 - 220" refId="ref4829" refString="Iharos, G. (1936) Zwei neue Tardigraden-Arten. Zoologischer Anzeiger, 115, 218 - 220." type="journal article" year="1936">
Iharos, 
<quantity box="[976,1034,808,834]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.91744" pageId="6" unit="in" value="1936.0">1936</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in details of the plate sculpture (pores various in shape in 
<taxonomicName authority="Pilato &amp; Binda &amp; Lisi, 2005" authorityName="Pilato &amp; Binda &amp; Lisi" authorityYear="2005" box="[741,866,848,873]" class="Heterotardigrada" family="Echiniscidae" genus="Echiniscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Echiniscoidea" pageId="6" phylum="Tardigrada" rank="species" species="arthuri" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[741,866,848,873]" italics="true" pageId="6">E. arthuri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[883,985,847,873]" pageId="6">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[883,985,847,873]" pageId="6" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, regular granulation in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Iharos" authorityYear="1936" class="Heterotardigrada" family="Echiniscidae" genus="Echiniscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Echiniscoidea" pageId="6" phylum="Tardigrada" rank="species" species="bartramiae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6">E. bartramiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and in having appendages C and D shorter (spines instead of filaments). 
<bibRefCitation author="Iharos, G." box="[264,421,928,954]" pageId="6" pagination="218 - 220" refId="ref4829" refString="Iharos, G. (1936) Zwei neue Tardigraden-Arten. Zoologischer Anzeiger, 115, 218 - 220." type="journal article" year="1936">Iharos (1936)</bibRefCitation>
did not specify whether smooth bands are present on some plates, and he did not specify whether spurs are present on the internal claws or not.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[264,1323,283,1274]" pageId="6">
<taxonomicName authority="Pilato &amp; Binda &amp; Lisi, 2005" authorityName="Pilato &amp; Binda &amp; Lisi" authorityYear="2005" box="[312,433,1008,1033]" class="Heterotardigrada" family="Echiniscidae" genus="Echiniscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Echiniscoidea" pageId="6" phylum="Tardigrada" rank="species" species="arthuri" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[312,433,1008,1033]" italics="true" pageId="6">E. arthuri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[445,545,1007,1033]" pageId="6">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[445,545,1007,1033]" pageId="6" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Richters, 1904 a" authorityName="Richters" authorityYear="1904" box="[720,1093,1008,1034]" class="Heterotardigrada" family="Echiniscidae" genus="Echiniscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Echiniscoidea" pageId="6" phylum="Tardigrada" rank="species" species="merokensis">
<emphasis box="[720,889,1008,1033]" italics="true" pageId="6">E. merokensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Richters, F." box="[902,1093,1008,1034]" pageId="6" pagination="493 - 508" refId="ref5027" refString="Richters, F. (1904 a) Arktischen Tardigraden. Fauna arctica, 3, 493 - 508." type="journal article" year="1904">Richters, 1904a</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but we examined specimens of this species from many localities (
<collectingCountry box="[847,903,1048,1074]" name="Italy" pageId="6">Italy</collectingCountry>
, North Africa, 
<collectingCountry box="[1089,1188,1048,1074]" name="Ecuador" pageId="6">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, Tierra del Fuego) and have noted some constant differences between the species here compared. In 
<taxonomicName authority="Pilato &amp; Binda &amp; Lisi, 2005" authorityName="Pilato &amp; Binda &amp; Lisi" authorityYear="2005" box="[264,380,1128,1153]" class="Heterotardigrada" family="Echiniscidae" genus="Echiniscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Echiniscoidea" pageId="6" phylum="Tardigrada" rank="species" species="arthuri" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[264,380,1128,1153]" italics="true" pageId="6">E. arthuri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[389,484,1127,1153]" pageId="6">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[389,484,1127,1153]" pageId="6" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
the plate sculpture is of the same 
<typeStatus box="[891,941,1128,1154]" pageId="6">type</typeStatus>
(pores) on all plates while in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Richters" authorityYear="1904" class="Heterotardigrada" family="Echiniscidae" genus="Echiniscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Echiniscoidea" pageId="6" phylum="Tardigrada" rank="species" species="merokensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6">E. merokensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, on the anterior portion of the paired plates II and III and on the anterior portion of the median plate 2, very few or no pores are present (
<figureCitation box="[1013,1112,1208,1234]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[264,368,1797,1821]" captionTargetBox="[394,1193,313,1781]" captionTargetId="figure-56@4.[394,1194,312,1781]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. A, B: Echiniscus arthuri sp. nov. (holotype): A, details of the plate sculpture; B, claws of the first three pairs of legs. C: Echiniscus merokensis, details of the plate sculpture. Scale bar = 10 m." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5050057" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5050057/files/figure.png" pageId="6">Fig. 3 C</figureCitation>
); in 
<taxonomicName authority="Pilato &amp; Binda &amp; Lisi, 2005" authorityName="Pilato &amp; Binda &amp; Lisi" authorityYear="2005" box="[1164,1280,1208,1233]" class="Heterotardigrada" family="Echiniscidae" genus="Echiniscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Echiniscoidea" pageId="6" phylum="Tardigrada" rank="species" species="arthuri" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1164,1280,1208,1233]" italics="true" pageId="6">E. arthuri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="6">
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="6" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
no smooth band is present on the scapular and terminal plates.
</paragraph>
